PDU = "Power Distribution Unit". 

Although a simple concept, the device which this acronym describes takes many forms.  The most basic would be those "Power Strips" you can buy just about anywhere which converts one outlet, to many.  Most of us own at least a few.  

But as with everything, they can vary greatly in terms of features and reliability - from simple "glue and go" models better for nothing more than an extra place to plug in your hairdryer, to military-grade devices mounted into industrial server racks, handling conditioned power with remote control capability via serial port and more.  

Just about all of them have a built-in breaker switch in order to prevent overload from popping a breaker at the switchbox.  
This is good.  :-)